# Getting started with provider data API (persistent)

This guide covers setting up and running the provider data API (persistent) locally.

## Prerequisites

- Java 25 or later
- Gradle (recommend using the included Gradle wrapper)

## Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ministryofjustice/laa-provider-data-platform.git
cd laa-provider-data-platform
```

## Build from source

Build the application:

```bash
./gradlew clean build
```

Run integration tests:

```bash
./gradlew integrationTest
```

## Run the application

Start the application locally:

```bash
./gradlew bootRun
```

## Application endpoints

### REST API documentation

- Swagger UI: [http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html](http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html)
- OpenAPI specification (JSON): [http://localhost:8080/v3/api-docs](http://localhost:8080/v3/api-docs)

### Actuator endpoints

- [http://localhost:8080/actuator](http://localhost:8080/actuator)
- [http://localhost:8080/actuator/health](http://localhost:8080/actuator/health)

## Run end-to-end tests

```bash
./gradlew :provider-data-e2e:e2eTest -Penv=local -Dauth.token=Dummy1
```

## Build container image

```bash
./gradlew bootBuildImage
```

## Libraries used

- [Spring Boot Actuator](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/reference/actuator/index.html) -
  Application monitoring endpoints
- [Spring Boot Web](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/reference/web/index.html) - REST API
  implementation
- [Spring Data JPA](https://docs.spring.io/spring-data/jpa/reference/jpa.html) - Database access
  abstraction
- [Springdoc OpenAPI](https://springdoc.org/) - OpenAPI documentation generation
- [MapStruct](https://mapstruct.org/) - Object mapping between DTOs and entities
